ygData.subject: RE: Play Time?
ygData.msgSnippet: Halana s (the Shaman) played time (level 46) is like 50 days (OUCH! but she has spent many days camping stuff, or just goofing). Tani s (the Bard) played time
ygData.messageBody:
Halana's (the Shaman) played time (level 46) is like 50 days
(OUCH! but she has spent many days camping stuff, or just goofing).

Tani's (the Bard) played time (level 17) is like 7 days or
so... I was much more focused....

Mirra (the Monkette) at level 15 is like 2.5 days or so...

Hmm, I'm not going to calculate the actual hours played,
that might be too frightening and force me to like get a life or
something...

And for the record, I'm employed full time but have no life
:-)

-----Original Message-----
From: David Nolle [mailto:dnolle@...]
Sent: Wednesday, January 26, 2000 9:45 PM
To: eqbards@onelist.com
Subject: [eqbards] Play Time?

From: David Nolle <dnolle@...>

Alright, I've been reading this list for a
long time and been playing EQ
since about three weeks after release. It
simply blows my mind that anyone
could have a 50th Level character, let alone
more than one! I've got three
characters, each on a different server:

Pendor, 12 Level Paladin (4 days, played, my
first character ever)
Windsinger Legendmaker, 24th Level Bard (22
days Played, favorite)
Nona, 7th lvl enchanter (6 hours played,
this weekend...grin)

I thought this much time played (678 hours)
meant I was a complete addict!
I just have to know what the play time is on
a few "high" (>40) level
characters. Is everybody un-employed, rich,
or just way smarter players
than I (I sure don't rule that out...grin)?
I'm not trolling...just bloody
well amazed and curious (and obviously
jealous).
